ItemDescription: excrement accumulation (other than that normally associated with
gathering or removal of plant products
drag scarification (anchor chain or shark fin)
terrain failures (active/recent slumps, slides, solifluction, etc.)
inundation (including temporary inundation resulting from beaver activity)
temporary seepage (usually artificially induced; excludes intermittent seepage resulting from climate
water table depression (associated with extensive water extraction from wells)
Miscellaneous (For other disturbance types, enter “X” and describe under “Notes")
